{"id":4079,"date":"2019-02-27T14:31:10","date_gmt":"2019-02-27T14:31:10","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/?p=4079"},"modified":"2021-06-11T06:59:06","modified_gmt":"2021-06-11T06:59:06","slug":"version-2-3-0","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/version-2-3-0\/","title":{"rendered":"Version 2.3.0 &#8211; Major Update"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p> You may want to check the&nbsp;<a href=\"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/version-2-3-0\/#upgrading_notes\">upgrading notes<\/a>&nbsp;below <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"> <strong>Changelog<\/strong> <\/h2>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><li>Converted all tables to InnoDB engine.<\/li><li>Added ability to create modules.<\/li><li>Refactored the code to be more compatible with modules.<\/li><li>Added new hooks system.<\/li><li>Added role in staff table.<\/li><li>Added ability to record refunds on credit note.<\/li><li>Added staff members list that are using role when editing role.<\/li><li>Added hundreds of custom classes in the customers are for easier styling changes via custom.css<\/li><li>Added ability to add custom css in Setup-&gt;Theme Style, for admin area, customers area, and both.<\/li><li>Added spam filters for leads email integration.<\/li><li>Updated Codeigniter to 3.1.10<\/li><li>Fixed items order not working<\/li><li>Fixed images uploaded for contracts and proposals from mobile not showing<\/li><li>Fixed newsfeed new post notification not clickable.<\/li><li>Fixed reCaptcha going out of the container on some screen widths.<\/li><li>Fixed can&#8217;t select web to lead form empty default country field.<\/li><li>Fixed task notification link not working on iPad.<\/li><li>Fixed staff member still receive notification after removed from the task.<\/li><li>Fixed task comment download attachment in .zip<\/li><li>Fixed survey email lists custom field as a slug in the description.<\/li><li>Fixed web to lead form sometimes breaks the JSON.<\/li><li>Fixed {lead_source} merge field not replaced.<\/li><li>Fixed staff subscription merge fields not replaced.<\/li><li>Fixed new contact creation on NGINX conflict.<\/li><li>Fixed\/Enhanced regular staff can disable administrator when the staff has all staff permissions.<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"upgrading_notes\">Upgrading to version 2.3.0<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Perfex CRM version 2.3.0 is major version and comes with a lot changes in the code and the way how some features work.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>In order to make Perfex CRM more modular, in v.2.3.0 we needed to refactor the code for many of the features, this is the initial version where Perfex CRM will start to support third party modules to be integrated in the core, in future we have plans even for more changes and enhancements to follow more modern coding practice.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"> Main Menu and Setup Menu Reset <\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>The main admin menu and setup menu will be reset after upgrade to the initial Perfex CRM configuration<\/strong>, this menu code is fully refactored so modules can inject custom menu items.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you still want to apply your previous configuration, you can still do this in <strong>Setup-&gt;Menu Setup-&gt;Main Menu<\/strong>, just now you won&#8217;t be able to drag the menu items on the right side as inactive.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"725\" height=\"462\" src=\"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/perfexcrm-main-menu-disable.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4080\" srcset=\"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/perfexcrm-main-menu-disable.png 725w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/perfexcrm-main-menu-disable-300x191.png 300w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/perfexcrm-main-menu-disable-60x38.png 60w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/perfexcrm-main-menu-disable-150x96.png 150w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 725px) 100vw, 725px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Custom customers area theme<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>NOTE: You don&#8217;t need to perform this action if you are not using custom theme for the customers area.<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>If <\/strong>you are using <a href=\"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/customers-templates\/\"><g class=\"gr_ gr_4 gr-alert gr_gramm gr_inline_cards gr_run_anim Grammar only-ins replaceWithoutSep\" id=\"4\" data-gr-id=\"4\">custom<\/g> theme<\/a> for your <g class=\"gr_ gr_6 gr-alert gr_gramm gr_inline_cards gr_run_anim Grammar multiReplace\" id=\"6\" data-gr-id=\"6\">customers<\/g> area you will need to perform <g class=\"gr_ gr_11 gr-alert gr_gramm gr_inline_cards gr_run_anim Grammar multiReplace\" id=\"11\" data-gr-id=\"11\">a cha<\/g>nge in order your custom theme to work properly.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>In <strong>application\/views\/themes\/[THEME_NAME]\/index.php&nbsp;find:<\/strong><br> <br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>echo $scripts; <\/code><\/pre>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Replace with:<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>app_customers_footer();\napp_js_alerts();<\/code><\/pre>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">New Hooks System\ufeff<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Prior to Perfex CRM version 2.3.0, we used outdated hooks library that was used only for actions in the system and without the ability to create actually filters for the content like WordPress has. In this version, you will be able to create actions and filters with just a simple function.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>We refactored a lot of actions\/hooks to filters in order to comply with our new hooks system\/<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The hooks\/actions <strong>do_action <\/strong>and <strong>add_action <\/strong>are deprecated and won&#8217;t be longer used if you are using any e.q. in <strong class=\"\"><g class=\"gr_ gr_70 gr-alert gr_gramm gr_hide gr_inline_cards gr_run_anim Grammar only-ins multiReplace replaceWithoutSep replaceWithoutSep\" id=\"70\" data-gr-id=\"70\">my_functions_helper.php<\/g><\/strong><strong> <\/strong>file you should re-check them and find the new appropriate hooks. The old hooks will still work if you are using any, however, it&#8217;s strongly recommended you to update your code.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can use the new hooks feature like:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>hooks()-&gt;apply_filters($tag, $value, $additionalParams)\nhooks()-&gt;add_filter($tag, $function_to_add, $priority = 10, $accepted_args = 1);\nhooks()-&gt;add_action($tag, $function_to_add, $priority = 10, $accepted_args = 1)\nhooks()-&gt;do_action($tag, $arg = '')<\/code><\/pre>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">PHP Version<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p><g class=\"gr_ gr_14 gr-alert gr_spell gr_inline_cards gr_run_anim ContextualSpelling replaceWithoutSep\" id=\"14\" data-gr-id=\"14\"><strong>The the minimum<\/strong><\/g><strong> required PHP version for Perfex CRM is <\/strong><g class=\"gr_ gr_13 gr-alert gr_gramm gr_inline_cards gr_run_anim Punctuation only-del replaceWithoutSep\" id=\"13\" data-gr-id=\"13\"><strong>5.6.4<\/strong>,<\/g> if you are using <g class=\"gr_ gr_10 gr-alert gr_gramm gr_inline_cards gr_run_anim Grammar only-ins replaceWithoutSep\" id=\"10\" data-gr-id=\"10\">older<\/g> version the PHP 5.6.4 we strongly recommend you to update to newest PHP version like 7.1, 7.2 or 7.3. Keep in mind that we recommend for a reason to use <g class=\"gr_ gr_12 gr-alert gr_gramm gr_inline_cards gr_run_anim Grammar only-ins replaceWithoutSep\" id=\"12\" data-gr-id=\"12\">newest<\/g> version of PHP because in future updates Perfex CRM minimum  <br><g class=\"gr_ gr_15 gr-alert gr_gramm gr_inline_cards gr_run_anim Style multiReplace\" id=\"15\" data-gr-id=\"15\"><g class=\"gr_ gr_11 gr-alert gr_gramm gr_inline_cards gr_run_anim Grammar only-ins doubleReplace replaceWithoutSep\" id=\"11\" data-gr-id=\"11\">requirement<\/g>  for<\/g> PHP will be 7.1+.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Few features extracted as modules<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The features, <strong>Surveys<\/strong>, <strong>Database Backup,<\/strong> <strong>Goals<\/strong>, <strong>Theme Style<\/strong> (Setup-&gt;Theme Style), <strong>Menu Setup<\/strong> (Setup-&gt;Menu Setup) are extracted into separate modules (will still come with the purchase)<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>They can be found in <strong>Setup-&gt;Modules<\/strong>, where you can activate\/deactivate them.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Having problems?<\/strong><\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p>We are always striving to help our customers in case you are experiencing some issues with Perfex CRM, in case you are experiencing some issue don\u2019t hesitate to\u00a0<a href=\"https:\/\/my.perfexcrm.com\">open support ticket<\/a>\u00a0or if you want to report a possible bug and your support is expired, you can contact us at info@perfexcrm.com we will be happy to take a look.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Don\u2019t forget to include enough information in your ticket\/email so we can faster identify the issue, additionally, you may&nbsp;want to turn debug mode as explained&nbsp;<a href=\"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/faq\/how-to-set-debug-mode\/\">here<\/a>&nbsp;to get any error messages outputted.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>You may want to check the&nbsp;upgrading notes&nbsp;below Changelog Converted all tables to InnoDB engine. Added ability to create modules. Refactored the code to be more compatible with modules. Added new hooks system. Added role in staff table. Added ability to record refunds on credit note. Added staff members list that are using role when editing [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[23],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-4079","post","type-post","status-publish","forma